<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1299">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/10612.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Stadden</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Manzanillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Governor of the State of Colima called a meeting of residents of
                            Colima on the seventeenth instant demanding that 100,000 pesos be
                            furnished at once saying if not furnished voluntarily he would collect
                            by some means. Demonstration caused by the demand, opposition and
                            uprising probable. Representatives of American companies and interests
                            request information as to whether they shall contribute or refuse to
                            contribute. Embassy advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stadden</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>